One agent solution: ```The base of the pyramid is a square with side length 2, so its area is $2^2 = 4$. The height of the pyramid is the distance from the center of the base to the apex, which is the distance from the center of the cube to one of its vertices. Drawing a diagonal of the square base, we can see that the distance from the center to a vertex is $\sqrt{2}$ times the side length, or $2\sqrt{2}$.

[asy]
