The first step is to find the radius of the cylinder and cone. Since the diameter of the base is 10 meters, the radius is 5 meters. 

Let the height of the cone be $h$. According to the problem, the height of the cylinder is twice the height of the cone, so the height of the cylinder is $2h$. 

The volume of the cylinder is $\pi r^2 h$, and the volume of the cone is $\frac13\pi r^2 h$. So the total volume of the silo is:

\begin{align*}
\text{Volume}&= \text{Volume of cylinder + Volume of cone} \\
&= \pi r^2 (2h) + \frac13\pi r^2 (h) \\
&= \pi r^2 \left(2h + \frac13 h\right) \\
&= \pi r^2 \left(\frac{7}{3}h\right)
\end{align*}

Substituting $r=5$ and $2h=27-h$ (since $h$ is half the height of the cylinder), we get:

\begin{align*}
\text{Volume}&= \pi (5^2) \left(\frac{7}{3} \cdot \frac{27}{2}\right) \\
&= \pi (25) \left(\frac{7}{6} \cdot 27\right) \\
&= \boxed{\frac{4725}{2}\pi} \text{ cubic meters}
\end{align*}

